This week the interim SABC board told Parliament that an R11m bonus paid to Hlaudi Motsoeneng will be probed by the SIU. JOHANNESBURG - Hlaudi Motsoeneng s lawyer says he s not aware of any investigation by the Special Investigating Unit (SIU) into the axed South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) COO s R11 million bonus. Motsoeneng was found guilty of misconduct and bringing the national broadcaster into disrepute by a disciplinary committee after holding an unauthorised four-hour-long press conference in April while he was on suspension.WATCH: The press conference that ended Hlaudi s SABC tenureMotsoeneng has been given a 30-day termination period. This week the interim board told Parliament that an R11 million bonus paid to Motsoeneng will be probed by the SIU because the payment did not follow proper governance processes. Motsoeneng s lawyer Zola Majavu says: I m unaware of that investigation and I consequently have no instructions and therefore I cannot comment on the situation. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)